Nineteen males of
indica
collected in various locations in India were examined. Coloration is like that of females. Head : Maxillary palpus slightly longer than proboscis, dark brown, pale yellowish at joints, extensive mottling of pale scales, palpomere 3 with dense long setae, some longer than palpomere 4, palpomeres 4 and 5 with short setae. Thorax : As in female. Abdomen : Terga as in female. Genitalia : Tergum VIII with cluster of 7–17 short stout setae on median caudal margin ( Fig. 2E ) (2–10 setae on median caudal margin in
alaskaensis
). Lobes of tergum IX slightly raised, separated by less than width of 1 lobe, each bearing an irregular row of 6–15 long slender setae. Sternum IX with 2–4 setae on apical margin. Gonocoxite long and cylindrical, length about 2.5 width at mid-length, with many long setae on dorsal surface, with short setae on dorso-apical area. Phallosome long, cylindrical, with rounded apex, hooked subapically, consisting of 2 sclerotized plates open dorsally and ventrally ( Fig. 2D ) (long, cylindrical, narrowed and hooked at apex in
alaskaensis
). Basal mesal lobe small, conical, sclerotized, bearing 2 stout setae apically and many shorter setae, 2 stout setae bent at about mid-length ( Fig. 2A ) (the 2 stout setae bent at about distal two-thirds from base in
alaskaensis
). Apical lobe small, rounded, sclerotized, bearing many setae nearly uniform in length, majority of specimens with 1‒4 somewhat stout and long setae on apical margin ( Fig. 2B ) (apical lobe with more or less uniform setae in
alaskaensis
). Proctiger sclerotized, with 4–6 dark teeth at apex and a group of 4–7 small setae on inner margin ( Fig. 2C ). Gonostylus about half length of gonocoxite, curved, tapered apically, bearing small setae; claw short, stout, bifurcated.

